# Line-ending and evidence handling for the legacy SQL -> PostgreSQL refactor.
#
# Scoped INTENTIONALLY to the artifacts this change owns. This is deliberately NOT
# a repository-wide `* text=auto` renormalization: the surrounding StockSharp tree
# keeps its existing per-file conventions untouched (minimal-change discipline,
# AAP 0.7.2), and only the files introduced or migrated by this refactor are pinned.

# --- QA evidence (see QA/README.md "File handling") ---------------------------------
# Screenshots are binary PNGs: never diffed, never line-ending-normalized.
QA/screenshots/*.png binary
# The "recordings" are small TEXT transcripts (a sanctioned substitute for video,
# AAP 0.7.2), not binary media. They are pinned to LF so they stay diff-able and
# searchable in review. This is exactly why Git LFS is NOT used for them - tracking
# small, reviewable text in LFS would make it opaque. See QA/README.md.
QA/recordings/*.md text eol=lf
QA/README.md         text eol=lf

# --- migrated data-access project file ----------------------------------------------
# Authored with LF (its original repository convention); pinned so editors/tooling
# cannot silently reintroduce a CRLF flip on the migrated PackageReference block
# (review finding N3).
Algo/Algo.csproj text eol=lf
